<item>
            <title>[LU-19218] DKMS use common.postinst if it is available</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19218</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When building diskless images for deployment the kernel owning the chroot&lt;br/&gt;
may be different from the kernel the chroot is to deployed on.&lt;br/&gt;
In such cases the default of falling back to $(uname -r) results in a image that&lt;br/&gt;
cannot be deployed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For such deployment a common.postinst is still used to run dkms build/install with&lt;br/&gt;
the correct kernel. So prefer to run common.postinst if it exists.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;common.postinst script is used when building in chroot for&lt;br/&gt;
diskless deployment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fixes: a2b5118f2a (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18533&quot; title=&quot;lustre-dkms.spec.in WARNING: /usr/lib/dkms/common.postinst does not exist.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18533&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18533&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; build: fix the common.postinst nonexistence issue&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
